    "description": "Two-step Timelock batch executed by the Lumina Safe (0xa17e8b7f985022BC3c607e9c4858A1C264b33cFD). The Safe is the proposer+executor of the TimelockController (0xd0De5D53dCA2D96cdE7FAf540BA3f3a44fdB747a), which is the actual owner of CoverRouter and LuminaOracle. Because TimelockController.minDelay = 0, schedule and execute can run in the same Safe transaction. This batch wraps 10 inner operations: (1) UUPS-upgrade CoverRouter to 0xFCb89188EBcb16D122aa1f5615C2ae3C2E726d05; (2) re-point Depeg/IL/Exploit productIds to V2 shields; (3) re-activate the 3 products; (4) register USDC/USDT/DAI literal bytes32-string feeds in LuminaOracle so DepegShield can query the oracle. Salt = keccak256(\"LUMINA-UPGRADE-2026-04-07-DEPEG-IL-EXPLOIT-V2\"). Predecessor = 0x00 (no dependency).",
